TV series)|''Feud'']]: ''Bette and Joan''; [[FX (TV channel)|FX]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{IMDb name|0188266}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20160109164945/http://darkestnight.strangely-funny.net/ darkestnight: the works of Alain Boubil & Claude-Michel Sch\u00f6nberg]\n*[http://www.broadwayworld.com/viewcolumn.cfm?colid=19391 ''BroadwayWorld.com'' interview with Anthony Crivello, June 23, 2007]\n*Louis and Keely Finds its Louis and Keely [http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/theater/news/chi-louis-keely-chicago-cast-story.html]\n*Tony Award Winner Anthony Crivello Joins Studio Tenn [https://web.archive.org/web/20170208133903/http://www.tpac.org/spotlight/tony-award-winner-anthony-crivello-is-evitas-juan-peron/]\n*Frank Rich  Review of Evita https://www.nytimes.com/1982/10/17/theater/in-the-arts-critics-choice-229254.html\n\n{{TonyAward MusicalFeaturedActor 1976-2000}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Crivello, Anthony}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male musical theatre actors]]\n[[Category:Marquette University alumni]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Milwaukee]]\n[[Category:Tony Award winners]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toDemo(link changed toDemo (music); link changed toDemo (music); link changed toDemo (music); link changed toDemo (music); link changed toDemo (music)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthony_Crivello"}
{"title_page": "Dental instrument", "text_new": "[[Image:Dentalmirror09-10-05.jpg|150px|right|thumb|[[Mouth mirror]], a commonly used dental instrument]]\n'''Dental instruments''' are [[tools]] that dental professionals use to provide dental treatment. They include tools to examine, manipulate, treat, restore and remove [[teeth]] and surrounding [[mouth|oral]] structures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://faculty.atu.edu/cbrucker/Engl2053/Samples/DGA03.htm|title=Classification of Dental Instruments|last=|first=|date=|website=Arkansas Tech University|publisher=|access-date=2017-01-12}}</ref>\n\n==Examination instruments ==\nThese tools allow dental professionals to manipulate tissues for better visual access during treatment or during dental examination.\n\n=== Dental Mirror===\n{{Main|Mouth mirror}}\nDental mirrors are used by the [[dentist]] or [[dental auxiliary]] to view a mirror image of the teeth in locations of the mouth where visibility is difficult or impossible. They also are used for reflecting light onto desired surfaces, indirect vision, and with retraction of soft tissues to improve access or vision.\n\n===Probes===\n*[[Dental explorer]] (sickle probe) \n*[[Periodontal probe]]\n*[https://www.adentalls.com/product-category/disposable-sterilization/.html For more information]\n\n==Retractors==\n[[File:Cheek retractor.jpg|thumb|180px|Cheek retractor]]\n*[[Mouth prop]] \n*Dental mirror \n*Cheek retractor\n*Tongue retractor \n*Lip retractor\n\n==Local anesthesia==\n*[[Dental anesthesia]] and [[dental syringe]]\n\nAnesthesia is broken down into three main categories: local, regional, and general, all of which affect the nervous system in some way and can be administered using various methods and different medications.\n\nLocal anesthesia is an anesthetic drug (which can be given as a shot, spray, or ointment) that numbs only a small, specific area of the body (for example, a foot, hand, or patch of skin). With local anesthesia, a person is awake while sedated. Local anesthesia lasts for a short period of time and is often used for minor outpatient procedures (when patients come in for surgery and can go home that same day). For someone having outpatient surgery in a clinic or doctor's office (such as the dentist or dermatologist), this anesthetic is likely used. The medicine can numb the area during the procedure and for a short time afterwards to help control post-surgery discomfort. \n\nThe function of this instrument involves successfully piercing the surface of the periodontal ligament so the patient can be distributed the anesthesia.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite patent|title=Dental instrument-PDL syringe|gdate=1983-05-20|url=https://patents.google.com/patent/US4444560A/en}}</ref> Past devices have proven to be insufficient because it instilled fear in patients and made it exhaustingly uncomfortable for dentists to use because of the bulky size.<ref name=\":0\" /> With how simple it is to hide it in the hand due to the smaller size of modern day anesthetic syringes, dentists are successfully able to maneuver in a patient's mouth without causing harm to the patient being treated, allowing for a quick insert of the anesthesia followed by the dentist being able move on swiftly to the next task of the dental visit.<ref name=\":0\" /> Another aspect of the syringe is the capability of use, which means dentists are able to easily insert fluid in the device and follow the color coded instructions that allow for efficient use of the dental instrument.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite patent|title=All purpose dental syringe|gdate=1981-10-26|url=https://patents.google.com/patent/US4472141A/en}}</ref> The device is so intricately sized that doctors are able to grip it well enough to get the job done.<ref name=\":1\" /> Some Anesthetic Syringes also include a power handle that gives the doctor less of a responsibility over the amount of pressure needed to push in the medicine because the power handle has settings that let the Dentist set an amount for how much anesthetic they want to be produced.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Dental handpieces==\n[[Image:Dentalhandpiece0111-26-05.jpg|right|300px|thumb|A high-speed [[dental handpiece]].]]\n{{Main|Dental drill}}\nDental handpieces come in many various types which include: High speed air driven (also known as an airotor), slow speed, friction grip, surgical hand piece.\n\n==Dental laser==\nA [[dental laser]] is a type of [[laser]] designed specifically for use in [[oral surgery]] or [[dentistry]].\n\nThe use of a laser can decrease [[morbidity]] after surgery, and reduces the need for [[anesthetics]]. Because of the [[cauterization]] of tissue there will be little bleeding following soft tissue procedures, and some risks of alternative [[electrosurgery]] procedures are avoided.\n\n==Dental torque wrench==\nA [[dental torque wrench]] or restorative torque wrench is a torque wrench used to precisely apply a specific [[torque]] to a fastener [[Screw#Bolt|bolt]] for fixation of an [[Abutment (dentistry)|abutment]], [[dentures]] or prosthetics on a [[dental implant]].<ref>{{Cite journal\n | author = [[Mahmood Kazemi]], [[Ahmad Rohanian]], [[Abbas Monzavi]] & [[Mohammad Sadegh Nazari]]\n | title = Evaluation of the accuracy and related factors of the mechanical torque-limiting device for dental implants\n | journal = [[Journal of dentistry (Tehran, Iran)]]\n | volume = 10\n | issue = 2\n | pages = 112\u2013118\n |date=March 2013\n | pmid = 23724209\n | pmc=3666070\n}}</ref>\n\n==Burs==\nDental Burs cutting surface are either made of a multifluted [[tungsten carbide]], a diamond coated tip, or a stainless steel multi fluted rosehead.\nThere are many different types and classifications of burs. Some of the most common are: the round bur (sizes \u00bc to 10) or inverted cone (sizes 33\u00bd to 90L).\nBurs are also classified by the type of shank. For instance a latch type, or right angle bur, is only used in the slow speed handpiece with contra-angle attachment. Long shank or shaft is only used in the slow speed when the contra-angle is not in use, and finally a friction grip bur, which is a small bur, is used only in the high-speed handpiece.\n\nThere are many bur shapes that are utilized in various specific procedures.\n\n===Operative burs===\nFlat fissure, pear-shaped, football, round, tapered, flame, chamfer, bevel, end cut,\nbud bur, steel, inverted cone, diamond, brown stone, and green-stone\n\n==Restorative instruments==\n\n===Excavators ===\n*Spoon excavator: Used to remove soft carious decay.\n*Half hollenbach: Used to test for overhangs or flash.\n*Dental hatchers: Used to widen the entrance of the tooth cavity and slice away the thin carious enamel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.drchetan.com/different-types-of-dental-excavators.html|title=Dental excavators|website=www.drchetan.com|access-date=2017-01-12}}</ref>\n*Chisels: \n**Straight - bevels the cavosurface margin and used in 3, 4 and 5 classifications of cavities on the maxillary.\n**Wedelstaedt - only used in the anterior for classes 3, 4 and 5 as well.\n**Bin Angle - this is held in a pen grasp and used for class 2 maxillary only.\n\n==Burnishers==\n*Flat plastic\n*Ball burnisher\n*Beavertail burnisher\n*Cone burnisher\n*Pear shaped burnisher\nBurnishers are used for polishing and contouring amalgam fillings and to polish   composite fillings.\n\n==Pluggers==\nPluggers are also known as amalgam condensers. They are used to achieve a well condensed filling by compressing the filling material into the cavity and applying pressure.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nhsdentistlurgan.com/resouces/Ns%20Instruments-final.pdf|title=Common Instruments Used in Dental Examination|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n*Amalgam plugger\n*49 plugger\n\n==Periodontal instruments==\n===Fine scalers===\nThese are used in the removal of soft deposit. They include:\n*MF 4/5\n*Drury scalers\n*Fine excavators\nHeavy scalers \nAre seen as the scalers used in the removal for heavy tartar and stain which are not been removed by the fine scalers. They include:\n*Scaler 152\n*Jacquette 1\n*Jacquette 2\n*Jacquette 3\n*American pattern B\n*Excavator\n*Hoe scaler \n*Cushion scaler\n\n===Curettes===\n{{Main|Periodontal curette}}\nTypes include: \n*Universal curettes - these have a semicircular tip used at 90\u00b0 to the tooth root surface. \n*Gracey curettes - semicircle tipped, but one edge lower than the other. It is used at 70\u00b0 to the tooth root surface.\n\n==Prosthodontic instruments==\n\n===Removable prosthodontics===\n*Spatulas for mixing Dental plaster\n*Spatulas for mixing Impression materials\n*Mixing bowls\n*Glass mixing slab\n*Fox plane\n*Willis gauge\n*Calipers\n*Bunsen burner \n*Blow torch\n*Wax knife\n*Wax spatula\n*Wax carver\n*Lecrons carver\n*Articulators\n*Face bow\n\n==Extraction/surgical instruments==\n\n===Dental forceps===\nIn 1840, Sir John Tomes and his friend Evrard made the first pair of [[Forceps|dental forceps]].<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite journal |pmc = 2413440|year = 1957|last1 = Cope|first1 = Z.|title = Sir John Tomes\u2014A Great Dental Pioneer|journal = Annals of the Royal College of Surgeons of England|volume = 20|issue = 1|pages = 1\u201312|pmid = 13395278}}</ref> In 1841, Tomes posted an article to tell the whole world about his discovery of new forceps that have never been seen before, successfully becoming the creator of the forceps and the concept of forceps.<ref name=\":3\" /> In earlier times, or during the eighteenth and nineteenth centuries, elevators and pelicans were used as extraction devices because the idea of dental forceps did not exist, but the thought of extracting in the first place with some form of a tool was there.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite journal|last=Atkinson|first=H. F.|date=2002|title=Some Early Dental Extraction Instruments Including the Pelican, Bird or Axe?|journal=Australian Dental Journal|language=en|volume=47|issue=2|pages=90\u201393|doi=10.1111/j.1834-7819.2002.tb00310.x|issn=1834-7819}}</ref> With pelicans, their sharp talons were used to be placed down on the inside of the mouth near the gums while the elevator helped pull the tooth out of its socket. Then, a pair of pincers would do the rest of the job, wiggling the tooth out of the gum until the extraction was complete.<ref name=\":4\" />  The functionality of today's Dental Forceps come from the need to remove items from the mouth such as the cotton balls Dentists place next to a patient's teeth or the rubber bands a patient needs for their braces.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite patent|title=Dental forceps|gdate=2002-02-05|url=https://patents.google.com/patent/US20020106609A1/en}}</ref> However, most dental forceps are not designed for comfort, nor do they take the account of the dental practitioners hand positions throughout the procedure to mind.<ref name=\":2\" /> Dental forceps have been designed to the point where Dentists experience medical complications of their own on the carpal scale considering their hands are always placed in a certain awkward angle while they remove items from the patient's mouth.<ref name=\":2\" />\u00a0 \u00a0\n\n==== List of Dental Forceps ====\n\n*Cow horns #23\n*Upper universals\n*Upper universal fine\n*Lower universals\n*Upper canine \n*Upper straight long \n*Upper straight short \n*Upper right molar \n*Upper left molar \n*Upper wisdom tooth \n*Greyhound \n*Root \n*Bayonet\n\n===[[Elevator (dental)|Elevator]]s===<!-- This section is linked from [[Lever]] -->\n*Narrow and wide, straight and curved luxators\n*[[Coupland\u2019s elevators]]\n*Warwick James elevators\n*Cryer elevators\n*Winter elevators\n*Periosteal elevators\n*Molts elevators \n*Root-tip pick elevator\n*Heidbrink root tip elevators\n*Crane root tip elevators\n*Potts elevators\n*Cogswell-A & B elevators\n*Flat elevators\n*Miller's apex luxators\n*Crossbar apex luxators\n\n===Chisels===\n*[[Osteotome]]\n\n==Orthodontic instruments==\n*[[Ligature (orthodontic)|Ligature]]\n*Distal end cutters\n*Bracket holder\n*Band pusher\n*Band setter\n*Hemostat/Mathieu pliers\n*Bird Beak Piers \n*Distal End Cutter \n*Bracket Twizzer \n*Tucker \n*Cinch Back\n\n==Endodontic instruments==\n*K-files\n*Hedstrom or H-files\n*NiTi flex files\n*Pathfinder files\n*Manual tapered files\n*Rotary tapered files\n*Controlled memory flexible files\n*Gates glidden burs\n*Peeso reamer burs\n*Mcspadden files\n*Guttapercha retrieval files\n*Finger spreader\n*Finger pluggers\n*[[Lentulo spiral]] files\n*Broken instrument retrieval files\n*Masserans kit\n*Post and Core kit\n*Endodontic explorer\n*Apex locator\n*Microscope\n\n==See also==\n* [[Dentistry]]\n* [[Dentist]] & [[dental auxiliary]]\n* [https://www.adentalls.com/product-category/disposable-sterilization/.html Information about dental disposable and sterlization material]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Dentistry}}\n\n{{MedInst}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dental Instruments}}\n[[Category:Dental materials]]\n[[Category:Dental equipment]]\n[[Category:Medical equipment]]\n", "text_old": "[[Image:Dentalmirror09-10-05.jpg|150px|right|thumb|[[Mouth mirror]], a commonly used dental instrument]]\n'''Dental instruments''' are [[tools]] that dental professionals use to provide dental treatment. They include tools to examine, manipulate, treat, restore and remove [[teeth]] and surrounding [[mouth|oral]] structures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://faculty.atu.edu/cbrucker/Engl2053/Samples/DGA03.htm|title=Classification of Dental Instruments|last=|first=|date=|website=Arkansas Tech University|publisher=|access-date=2017-01-12}}</ref>\n\n==Examination instruments ==\nThese tools allow dental professionals to manipulate tissues for better visual access during treatment or during dental examination.\n\n=== Dental Mirror===\n{{Main|Mouth mirror}}\nDental mirrors are used by the [[dentist]] or [[dental auxiliary]] to view a mirror image of the teeth in locations of the mouth where visibility is difficult or impossible. They also are used for reflecting light onto desired surfaces, indirect vision, and with retraction of soft tissues to improve access or vision.\n\n===Probes===\n*[[Dental explorer]] (sickle probe) \n*[[Periodontal probe]]\n\n==Retractors==\n[[File:Cheek retractor.jpg|thumb|180px|Cheek retractor]]\n*[[Mouth prop]] \n*Dental mirror \n*Cheek retractor\n*Tongue retractor \n*Lip retractor\n\n==Local anesthesia==\n*[[Dental anesthesia]] and [[dental syringe]]\n\nAnesthesia is broken down into three main categories: local, regional, and general, all of which affect the nervous system in some way and can be administered using various methods and different medications.\n\nLocal anesthesia is an anesthetic drug (which can be given as a shot, spray, or ointment) that numbs only a small, specific area of the body (for example, a foot, hand, or patch of skin). With local anesthesia, a person is awake while sedated. Local anesthesia lasts for a short period of time and is often used for minor outpatient procedures (when patients come in for surgery and can go home that same day). For someone having outpatient surgery in a clinic or doctor's office (such as the dentist or dermatologist), this anesthetic is likely used. The medicine can numb the area during the procedure and for a short time afterwards to help control post-surgery discomfort. \n\nThe function of this instrument involves successfully piercing the surface of the periodontal ligament so the patient can be distributed the anesthesia.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite patent|title=Dental instrument-PDL syringe|gdate=1983-05-20|url=https://patents.google.com/patent/US4444560A/en}}</ref> Past devices have proven to be insufficient because it instilled fear in patients and made it exhaustingly uncomfortable for dentists to use because of the bulky size.<ref name=\":0\" /> With how simple it is to hide it in the hand due to the smaller size of modern day anesthetic syringes, dentists are successfully able to maneuver in a patient's mouth without causing harm to the patient being treated, allowing for a quick insert of the anesthesia followed by the dentist being able move on swiftly to the next task of the dental visit.<ref name=\":0\" /> Another aspect of the syringe is the capability of use, which means dentists are able to easily insert fluid in the device and follow the color coded instructions that allow for efficient use of the dental instrument.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite patent|title=All purpose dental syringe|gdate=1981-10-26|url=https://patents.google.com/patent/US4472141A/en}}</ref> The device is so intricately sized that doctors are able to grip it well enough to get the job done.<ref name=\":1\" /> Some Anesthetic Syringes also include a power handle that gives the doctor less of a responsibility over the amount of pressure needed to push in the medicine because the power handle has settings that let the Dentist set an amount for how much anesthetic they want to be produced.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Dental handpieces==\n[[Image:Dentalhandpiece0111-26-05.jpg|right|300px|thumb|A high-speed [[dental handpiece]].]]\n{{Main|Dental drill}}\nDental handpieces come in many various types which include: High speed air driven (also known as an airotor), slow speed, friction grip, surgical hand piece.\n\n==Dental laser==\nA [[dental laser]] is a type of [[laser]] designed specifically for use in [[oral surgery]] or [[dentistry]].\n\nThe use of a laser can decrease [[morbidity]] after surgery, and reduces the need for [[anesthetics]]. Because of the [[cauterization]] of tissue there will be little bleeding following soft tissue procedures, and some risks of alternative [[electrosurgery]] procedures are avoided.\n\n==Dental torque wrench==\nA [[dental torque wrench]] or restorative torque wrench is a torque wrench used to precisely apply a specific [[torque]] to a fastener [[Screw#Bolt|bolt]] for fixation of an [[Abutment (dentistry)|abutment]], [[dentures]] or prosthetics on a [[dental implant]].<ref>{{Cite journal\n | author = [[Mahmood Kazemi]], [[Ahmad Rohanian]], [[Abbas Monzavi]] & [[Mohammad Sadegh Nazari]]\n | title = Evaluation of the accuracy and related factors of the mechanical torque-limiting device for dental implants\n | journal = [[Journal of dentistry (Tehran, Iran)]]\n | volume = 10\n | issue = 2\n | pages = 112\u2013118\n |date=March 2013\n | pmid = 23724209\n | pmc=3666070\n}}</ref>\n\n==Burs==\nDental Burs cutting surface are either made of a multifluted [[tungsten carbide]], a diamond coated tip, or a stainless steel multi fluted rosehead.\nThere are many different types and classifications of burs. Some of the most common are: the round bur (sizes \u00bc to 10) or inverted cone (sizes 33\u00bd to 90L).\nBurs are also classified by the type of shank. For instance a latch type, or right angle bur, is only used in the slow speed handpiece with contra-angle attachment. Long shank or shaft is only used in the slow speed when the contra-angle is not in use, and finally a friction grip bur, which is a small bur, is used only in the high-speed handpiece.\n\nThere are many bur shapes that are utilized in various specific procedures.\n\n===Operative burs===\nFlat fissure, pear-shaped, football, round, tapered, flame, chamfer, bevel, end cut,\nbud bur, steel, inverted cone, diamond, brown stone, and green-stone\n\n==Restorative instruments==\n\n===Excavators ===\n*Spoon excavator: Used to remove soft carious decay.\n*Half hollenbach: Used to test for overhangs or flash.\n*Dental hatchers: Used to widen the entrance of the tooth cavity and slice away the thin carious enamel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.drchetan.com/different-types-of-dental-excavators.html|title=Dental excavators|website=www.drchetan.com|access-date=2017-01-12}}</ref>\n*Chisels: \n**Straight - bevels the cavosurface margin and used in 3, 4 and 5 classifications of cavities on the maxillary.\n**Wedelstaedt - only used in the anterior for classes 3, 4 and 5 as well.\n**Bin Angle - this is held in a pen grasp and used for class 2 maxillary only.\n\n==Burnishers==\n*Flat plastic\n*Ball burnisher\n*Beavertail burnisher\n*Cone burnisher\n*Pear shaped burnisher\nBurnishers are used for polishing and contouring amalgam fillings and to polish   composite fillings.\n\n==Pluggers==\nPluggers are also known as amalgam condensers. They are used to achieve a well condensed filling by compressing the filling material into the cavity and applying pressure.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nhsdentistlurgan.com/resouces/Ns%20Instruments-final.pdf|title=Common Instruments Used in Dental Examination|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n*Amalgam plugger\n*49 plugger\n\n==Periodontal instruments==\n===Fine scalers===\nThese are used in the removal of soft deposit. They include:\n*MF 4/5\n*Drury scalers\n*Fine excavators\nHeavy scalers \nAre seen as the scalers used in the removal for heavy tartar and stain which are not been removed by the fine scalers. They include:\n*Scaler 152\n*Jacquette 1\n*Jacquette 2\n*Jacquette 3\n*American pattern B\n*Excavator\n*Hoe scaler \n*Cushion scaler\n\n===Curettes===\n{{Main|Periodontal curette}}\nTypes include: \n*Universal curettes - these have a semicircular tip used at 90\u00b0 to the tooth root surface. \n*Gracey curettes - semicircle tipped, but one edge lower than the other. It is used at 70\u00b0 to the tooth root surface.\n\n==Prosthodontic instruments==\n\n===Removable prosthodontics===\n*Spatulas for mixing Dental plaster\n*Spatulas for mixing Impression materials\n*Mixing bowls\n*Glass mixing slab\n*Fox plane\n*Willis gauge\n*Calipers\n*Bunsen burner \n*Blow torch\n*Wax knife\n*Wax spatula\n*Wax carver\n*Lecrons carver\n*Articulators\n*Face bow\n\n==Extraction/surgical instruments==\n\n===Dental forceps===\nIn 1840, Sir John Tomes and his friend Evrard made the first pair of [[Forceps|dental forceps]].<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite journal |pmc = 2413440|year = 1957|last1 = Cope|first1 = Z.|title = Sir John Tomes\u2014A Great Dental Pioneer|journal = Annals of the Royal College of Surgeons of England|volume = 20|issue = 1|pages = 1\u201312|pmid = 13395278}}</ref> In 1841, Tomes posted an article to tell the whole world about his discovery of new forceps that have never been seen before, successfully becoming the creator of the forceps and the concept of forceps.<ref name=\":3\" /> In earlier times, or during the eighteenth and nineteenth centuries, elevators and pelicans were used as extraction devices because the idea of dental forceps did not exist, but the thought of extracting in the first place with some form of a tool was there.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite journal|last=Atkinson|first=H. F.|date=2002|title=Some Early Dental Extraction Instruments Including the Pelican, Bird or Axe?|journal=Australian Dental Journal|language=en|volume=47|issue=2|pages=90\u201393|doi=10.1111/j.1834-7819.2002.tb00310.x|issn=1834-7819}}</ref> With pelicans, their sharp talons were used to be placed down on the inside of the mouth near the gums while the elevator helped pull the tooth out of its socket. Then, a pair of pincers would do the rest of the job, wiggling the tooth out of the gum until the extraction was complete.<ref name=\":4\" />  The functionality of today's Dental Forceps come from the need to remove items from the mouth such as the cotton balls Dentists place next to a patient's teeth or the rubber bands a patient needs for their braces.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite patent|title=Dental forceps|gdate=2002-02-05|url=https://patents.google.com/patent/US20020106609A1/en}}</ref> However, most dental forceps are not designed for comfort, nor do they take the account of the dental practitioners hand positions throughout the procedure to mind.<ref name=\":2\" /> Dental forceps have been designed to the point where Dentists experience medical complications of their own on the carpal scale considering their hands are always placed in a certain awkward angle while they remove items from the patient's mouth.<ref name=\":2\" />\u00a0 \u00a0\n\n==== List of Dental Forceps ====\n\n*Cow horns #23\n*Upper universals\n*Upper universal fine\n*Lower universals\n*Upper canine \n*Upper straight long \n*Upper straight short \n*Upper right molar \n*Upper left molar \n*Upper wisdom tooth \n*Greyhound \n*Root \n*Bayonet\n\n===[[Elevator (dental)|Elevator]]s===<!-- This section is linked from [[Lever]] -->\n*Narrow and wide, straight and curved luxators\n*[[Coupland\u2019s elevators]]\n*Warwick James elevators\n*Cryer elevators\n*Winter elevators\n*Periosteal elevators\n*Molts elevators \n*Root-tip pick elevator\n*Heidbrink root tip elevators\n*Crane root tip elevators\n*Potts elevators\n*Cogswell-A & B elevators\n*Flat elevators\n*Miller's apex luxators\n*Crossbar apex luxators\n\n===Chisels===\n*[[Osteotome]]\n\n==Orthodontic instruments==\n*[[Ligature (orthodontic)|Ligature]]\n*Distal end cutters\n*Bracket holder\n*Band pusher\n*Band setter\n*Hemostat/Mathieu pliers\n*Bird Beak Piers \n*Distal End Cutter \n*Bracket Twizzer \n*Tucker \n*Cinch Back\n\n==Endodontic instruments==\n*K-files\n*Hedstrom or H-files\n*NiTi flex files\n*Pathfinder files\n*Manual tapered files\n*Rotary tapered files\n*Controlled memory flexible files\n*Gates glidden burs\n*Peeso reamer burs\n*Mcspadden files\n*Guttapercha retrieval files\n*Finger spreader\n*Finger pluggers\n*[[Lentulo spiral]] files\n*Broken instrument retrieval files\n*Masserans kit\n*Post and Core kit\n*Endodontic explorer\n*Apex locator\n*Microscope\n\n==See also==\n* [[Dentistry]]\n* [[Dentist]] & [[dental auxiliary]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Dentistry}}\n\n{{MedInst}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dental Instruments}}\n[[Category:Dental materials]]\n[[Category:Dental equipment]]\n[[Category:Medical equipment]]\n", "name_user": "Imranalfalah", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eSee also)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dental_instrument"}
{"title_page": "Michael Sam", "text_new": "{{for|the English criminal|Michael Sams}}\n{{pp-pc1|small=yes}}\n{{short description|American football defensive end}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Michael Sam\n| image               = Michael Sam final Mizzou home game.jpg\n| image_size          = 275\n| alt                 = \n| caption             = Sam holding a souvenir rock from the rock 'M' at [[Memorial Stadium (Columbia)|Memorial Stadium]] after a win against [[Texas A&M Aggies football|Texas A&M]]\n| current_team         = \n| number              = 96, 46, 94\n| position            = [[Defensive end]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1990|1|7}}\n| birth_place         = [[Galveston, Texas]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 2\n| weight_lbs          = 261\n| high_school         = [[Hitchcock High School|Hitchcock (TX)]]\n| college             = [[Missouri Tigers football|Missouri]]\n| draftyear           = 2014\n| draftround          = 7\n| draftpick           = 249\n| pastteams           = \n* [[St. Louis Rams]] ({{NFL Year|2014}})*\n* [[Dallas Cowboys]] ({{NFL Year|2014}})*\n* [[Montreal Alouettes]] ({{CFL Year|2015}})\n| pastteamsnote       = yes\n| status              = \n| highlights          = \n* Unanimous [[College Football All-America Team|All-American]] ([[2013 College Football All-America Team|2013]])\n* [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]] Defensive Player of the Year (2013)\n* First-team All-[[Southeastern Conference|SEC]] ([[2013 All-SEC football team|2013]])\n* Arthur Ashe Courage Award (2014)\n| nflnew              = michaelsam/2543734\n| pfr                 = S/SamxMi00\n| cfl                 = 8027\n}}\n'''Michael Alan Sam Jr.''' (born January 7, 1990) is an American former [[defensive end]] in [[American football|American]] and [[Canadian football]]. He played [[college football]] for the [[University of Missouri]] and was drafted by the [[St. Louis Rams]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL) in the seventh round of the [[2014 NFL draft]].\n\nSam was a consensus [[College Football All-America Team|All-American]] and the [[Southeastern Conference]] (SEC) Defensive Player of the Year as a senior at Missouri. After completing his college football career, Sam publicly [[coming out|came out]] as gay. He became the first publicly gay player to be drafted in the NFL. The Rams cut him during the final preseason roster cutdowns. He also spent time on the [[Dallas Cowboys]]' [[practice squad]] before being waived. He signed with the [[Montreal Alouettes]] before the 2015 season, and became the first publicly gay player to play in the [[Canadian Football League]] (CFL).\n\n==High school==\nSam attended [[Hitchcock High School]] in [[Hitchcock, Texas]]. He began traveling with the school's [[Varsity team#Varsity in North America|varsity]] [[American football|football]] team while in the eighth grade as a [[water boy]]. He later became a member of the team, playing [[defensive end]] and [[offensive tackle]].<ref name=rises>{{cite news |last=Palmer |first=Tod |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2013/11/07/4605096/missouris-michael-sam-rises-from.html |title=Missouri's Michael Sam rises from small Texas town to national star |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |date=November 7, 2013 |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe earned first-team All-District honors as a defensive lineman in all four years of high school, and as an offensive lineman in his junior and senior years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://texashsfootball.com/2014/02/09/former-hitchock-and-nfl-prospect-michael-sam-announces-he-is-gay/ |title=Former Hitchcock DE, NFL prospect Michael Sam announces he is gay |publisher=Texas HS Football |date= |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222212002/http://texashsfootball.com/2014/02/09/former-hitchock-and-nfl-prospect-michael-sam-announces-he-is-gay/ |archive-date=February 22, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> As a senior, Sam drew attention for his strong performance against [[Michael Brockers]] in a game against [[Ch\u00e1vez High School (Houston)|Ch\u00e1vez High School]]; Brockers, an [[All-America]]n, had accepted a scholarship to [[Louisiana State University]].<ref name=rises/><ref name=father/>\n\nOut of high school, Sam was considered a two-star [[college football]] recruit by ''[[Rivals.com]]''.<ref name=rises/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/ncaa/football/recruiting/player-Michael-Sam-63334 |title=Michael Sam \u2013 Yahoo! Sports |publisher=Sports.yahoo.com |date= |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref> He received scholarship offers from [[Arizona State University]], [[Colorado State University]], and the [[University of Houston]], but he wanted to attend [[Texas A&M University]], and waited for a scholarship offer from it.<ref name=unheralded>{{cite web|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/college-football/news/20140209/michael-sam-missouri-unheralded-recruit-unstoppable-force/|title=Michael Sam's rise from unheralded recruit to unstoppable SEC force|first=Andy|last=Staples|work=Sports Illustrated|date=February 9, 2014|accessdate=February 13, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nSam accepted a scholarship offer from the [[University of Missouri]] (Mizzou), after he was recruited by Craig Kuligowski, the team's [[defensive line coach]]. Kuligowski recruited other players near Hitchcock, which made him familiar with Sam.<ref name=unheralded/> Sam attended the school from 2009 to 2013. He played for the Tigers, competing in the [[Big 12 Conference]]. He [[redshirt (college sports)|redshirted]] in his first year at Missouri, and recorded 3.5 [[quarterback sack]]s, 24 [[tackle (football move)|tackle]]s, including seven [[tackles for loss]], two [[forced fumbles]], one [[interception]] and one blocked kick as a redshirt freshman.<ref name=rises/><ref name=unheralded/> In his sophomore year, Sam intercepted a [[forward pass|tipped pass]] in a game against the [[Texas Tech Red Raiders football|Texas Tech Red Raiders]], which secured a victory to make Mizzou [[bowl eligible]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lubbockonline.com/sports-red-raiders-football/2011-11-19/missouri-scores-late-saves-win-tipped-pass-interception#.UwZWqGJdVjc|title=Missouri scores late, saves win on tipped-pass interception: The Red Raiders have lost four in a row after Deoge's last-minute interception. Tuberville said a Tech victory \"just wasn't meant to be.\"|date=November 19, 2011|first=Don |last=Williams|work=Lubbock Avalanche-Journal|accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref> In 2012, Mizzou transferred to the [[Southeastern Conference]] (SEC). Sam registered {{frac|3|1|2}} sacks while starting in nine of the team's games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/blog/sec/post/_/id/76836/ten-sec-surprise-players-in-2013|title=Ten SEC surprise players in 2013|publisher=ESPN|date=December 20, 2013|first1=Ed |last1=Aschoff |first2=Chris |last2=Low|accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAs a senior in 2013, Sam recorded 11.5 quarterback sacks and 19 tackles for a loss. He led the SEC in both categories, and tied Missouri's single-season record for sacks.<ref>{{cite news |last=Palmer |first=Tod |url=http://www.kansascity.com/sports/college/sec/university-of-missouri/article338662/Teammate-proud-that-Michael-Sam-%E2%80%98had-the-courage-to-come-out%E2%80%99.html |title=Teammate proud that Michael Sam 'had the courage to come out' |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |date=February 9, 2014  |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref> He was named the SEC Defensive Player of the Week in two consecutive weeks, after recording three sacks apiece in games against the [[Arkansas State Red Wolves football|Arkansas State Red Wolves]] and the [[Vanderbilt Commodores football|Vanderbilt Commodores]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kansascity.com/2013/10/10/4543194/singing-joking-michael-sam-sets.html|title=Singing, joking Michael Sam sets the tone for Missouri's defensive line|date=October 10, 2013|first=Tod|last=Palmer|newspaper=The Kansas City Star|accessdate=February 13, 2014}}</ref> After the season, Sam was named the SEC Co-Defensive Player of the Year, with [[C. J. Mosley (linebacker)|C. J. Mosley]] of the [[University of Alabama]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.al.com/alabamafootball/index.ssf/2013/12/alabamas_cj_mosley_christion_j.html|title=Alabama's C.J. Mosley, Christion Jones win SEC player of the year awards|first= Michael |last=Casagrande|work=AL.com|date=December 11, 2013|accessdate=February 13, 2014}}</ref> and a first-team all-SEC selection.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kerkhoff |first=Blair |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2013/12/09/4681420/defensive-player-of-the-year-michael.html |title=Defensive player of the year Michael Sam leads four Tigers on all-SEC team |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |date=December 9, 2013 |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref>\n\nSam was named a first-team [[2013 College Football All-America Team|All-American]] by the [[Walter Camp Football Foundation]], [[Associated Press]], ''[[Sporting News]]'', the [[American Football Coaches Association]], and the [[Football Writers Association of America]].<ref name=accomplishments/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mutigers.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/121213aaa.html |title=Michael Sam Named First-Team All-American by Walter Camp: He Becomes the 33rd All-American in Mizzou Football History|work=mutigers.com|date=December 12, 2013|accessdate=May 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2013/12/12/4689056/missouris-michael-sam-is-walter.html |title=Missouri's Michael Sam is Walter Camp first-team All-American |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |date=December 12, 2013 |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=David |last=Eulitt |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2013/12/13/4690070/mizzous-michael-sam-is-two-for.html |title=Mizzou's Michael Sam is two for two on All-America teams |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |date=December 13, 2013 |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref> He was also named a semifinalist for the [[Chuck Bednarik Award]], the [[Hendricks Award]], and the [[Lombardi Award]].<ref name=rises/><ref name=accomplishments/> Missouri played in the [[2014 Cotton Bowl Classic]], in which Sam forced a fumble which was returned for a touchdown, securing Missouri's victory over the [[Oklahoma State Cowboys football|Oklahoma State Cowboys]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/blog/big12/post/_/id/78454/missouri-defends-sec-with-cotton-bowl-win|title=Mizzou defends SEC with Cotton Bowl win|date=January 4, 2014|first=Brandon |last=Chatmon | publisher=ESPN|accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref>\n\nDuring his college career, Sam accumulated 123 tackles, including 36 for loss, 21 sacks, six forced fumbles and two intercepted passes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mutigers.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/michael_sam_452639.html |title=Michael Sam bio |publisher=University of Missouri Official Athletic Site |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140404162150/http://www.mutigers.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/michael_sam_452639.html |archive-date=April 4, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He graduated from Missouri in December 2013.<ref name=nytimes /> He participated in the [[2014 Senior Bowl]] in January 2014; considered too small to play as a defensive end in the [[National Football League]] (NFL), he played as an [[outside linebacker]]. Sam struggled at the new position.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kansascity.com/2014/01/30/4787048/senior-bowl-losers-missouris-michael.html|title=Senior Bowl losers: Transition to linebacker tough for Missouri's Michael Sam|date=January 30, 2014|first=Terez A.|last=Paylor|work=The Kansas City Star|accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\n\n===2014 NFL Draft===\nEarly projections had Sam as a third- or fourth-round pick in the [[2014 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2014/02/09/4810596/michael-sam-defensive-star-of.html |title=Missouri football star Michael Sam announces he is gay |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |first=Vahe |last=Gregorian |date=February 9, 2014 |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref> His performance in the [[NFL Scouting Combine]] in February 2014 was seen as disappointing, which lowered expectations about whether he would be taken in the draft.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/draft2014/story/_/id/10912694/2014-nfl-draft-notable-players-available-third-day|title=Michael Sam still on draft board|publisher=ESPN|date=May 10, 2014|accessdate=May 10, 2014}}</ref> He was considered to be too small to play defensive end and too slow to play outside linebacker.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/football/michael-sam-drafted-rams-shares-kiss-boyfriend-article-1.1787804|title=Michael Sam shares emotional kiss with boyfriend after he's picked by St. Louis Rams in NFL draft: Saturday's selection made Sam the first openly gay player to be drafted into the league and prompted celebrations at gay bars stretching from Los Angeles to Queens|first1=Melissa|last1=Chan|first2=Rich|last2=Schapiro|first3=Larry|last3=McShane|work=New York Daily News|date=May 10, 2014|accessdate=May 11, 2014}}</ref> He showed improvement at a public workout a month later, but his pre-draft rankings ranged from 12th to 25th among defensive ends. At the [[2013 NFL Draft|2013 draft]], 33 defensive ends were selected overall, with 23 taken in the final four rounds.<ref>{{cite news|last=Pennington |first=Bill |title=Sam and League Share Uncomfortable Scrutiny |date=May 7, 2014 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/08/sports/football/michael-sam-adds-a-gay-subplot-to-the-nfl-draft.html?_r=0 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6PTcQ8KaL?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/08/sports/football/michael-sam-adds-a-gay-subplot-to-the-nfl-draft.html?_r=1 |archivedate=May 10, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{{NFL predraft\n|    height ft = 6\n|    height in = 2\n|       weight = 261\n|         dash = 4.91\n|    ten split = 1.75\n| twenty split = N/A\n|      shuttle = N/A\n|   cone drill = N/A\n|     vertical = 25.5\n|     broad ft = 9\n|     broad in = 6\n|        bench = 17\n|    wonderlic = N/A\n|     arm span = {{fraction|33|3|8}}\n|    hand span = {{fraction|9|3|8}}\n|         note = All values from NFL Combine<ref>{{cite web|author=Nolan Nawrocki |url=http://www.nfl.com/combine/profiles/michael-sam?id=2543734 |title=NFL Events: Combine Player Profiles \u2013 Michael Sam |publisher=Nfl.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===St. Louis Rams===\n[[File:Michael Sam 2014.jpg|thumb|Sam with the St. Louis Rams during the 2014 preseason]]\nThe [[St. Louis Rams]] drafted Sam in the seventh round, the 249th of 256 players selected in the 2014 draft. He became the first publicly gay player to be drafted into the NFL.<ref>{{cite news|last=Belson |first=Ken |title=In Historic Pick, Rams Take Michael Sam in Final Round of Draft |date=May 10, 2014 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/11/sports/football/michael-sam-picked-by-st-louis-rams-in-nfl-draft.html?_r=0 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6PUBcQr0j?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/11/sports/football/michael-sam-picked-by-st-louis-rams-in-nfl-draft.html?_r=1 |archivedate=May 11, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/05/10/us/football-michael-sam/|title=Michael Sam makes history: First openly gay player drafted in the NFL|first=Chelsea J. |last=Carter|work=CNN|date=May 10, 2014|accessdate=May 10, 2014}}</ref> In a statement, President [[Barack Obama]] said that he \"congratulates Michael Sam, the Rams and the NFL for taking an important step forward today in our Nation's journey\" and that \"[f]rom the playing field to the corporate boardroom, LGBT Americans prove every day that you should be judged by what you do and not who you are.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Sam becomes first openly gay player drafted into NFL|url=https://news.yahoo.com/sam-becomes-first-openly-gay-player-drafted-nfl-231726522--nfl.html|accessdate=May 11, 2014|newspaper=Yahoo! News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Obama congratulates Michael Sam, first openly gay player drafted by NFL|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/05/10/us/football-michael-sam/|accessdate=May 11, 2014|newspaper=CNN|date=May 10, 2014}}</ref> St. Louis Rams jerseys bearing his name became the second best selling rookie jerseys at the NFL's website behind [[Cleveland Browns]]' quarterback (and [[Heisman Trophy]] winner) [[Johnny Manziel]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Boren|first=Cindy | title=Michael Sam trails only Johnny Manziel in rookie jersey sales after NFL draft | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/early-lead/wp/2014/05/12/michael-sam-trails-only-johnny-manziel-in-jersey-sales-after-nfl-draft | accessdate=May 13, 2014|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|date=May 13, 2014}}</ref> During the period from April 1 through July 17, Sam's jersey ranked sixth in sales among all NFL players.<ref>{{cite news|last=Sessler |first=Marc |title=Browns' Johnny Manziel leads NFL in jersey sales |date=July 21, 2014 |work=NFL.com |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap2000000366369/printable/browns-johnny-manziel-leads-nfl-in-jersey-sales |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SDwAqIPG?url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap2000000366369/printable/browns-johnny-manziel-leads-nfl-in-jersey-sales |archivedate=August 30, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nSam made his professional debut on August 8, 2014, during the first preseason game against the [[New Orleans Saints]], where he made one tackle in the game on quarterback [[Ryan Griffin (quarterback)|Ryan Griffin]]. During the second preseason game against the [[Green Bay Packers]], Sam recorded his first professional sack where he sacked [[Matt Flynn]]. In preseason game 3 against the Cleveland Browns, Sam sacked Manziel. In four exhibition games, Sam recorded 11 tackles and 3 sacks, including a team-leading 6 tackles in the final game. \"I believe he can play in this league\", Rams coach [[Jeff Fisher]] said.<ref name=farmer>{{cite news|last=Farmer |first=Sam |title=Michael Sam, NFL's first openly gay player, is cut by St. Louis Rams |date=August 30, 2014 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |url=https://www.latimes.com/sports/sportsnow/la-sp-sn-michael-sam-rams-20140830-story.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SDpHjHx0?url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/sportsnow/la-sp-sn-michael-sam-rams-20140830-story.html |archivedate=August 30, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> On August 30, St. Louis released Sam as part of a final round of cuts to reduce their roster to the league-mandated 53 players before the start of the regular season.<ref name=farmer/><ref name=wagoner/> The Rams, who kept nine defensive linemen, chose to retain undrafted rookie [[Ethan Westbrooks]] over Sam.<ref name=wagoner>{{cite news|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/11431047/michael-sam-cut-st-louis-rams|title=Michael Sam cut by Rams|date=August 30, 2014|first=Nick |last=Wagoner | publisher=ESPN|accessdate=August 30, 2014}}</ref> While their statistics were similar, Westbrooks provided the versatility to play all four defensive line positions, while Sam had been playing virtually exclusively as a left defensive end.<ref>{{cite news|last=Wagoner |first=Nick |title=Sam simply on wrong side of numbers |date=August 30, 2014 |publisher=ESPN |url=http://espn.go.com/blog/st-louis-rams/post/_/id/11070/sam-simply-on-wrong-side-of-numbers |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SEQFhnu1?url=http://espn.go.com/blog/st-louis-rams/post/_/id/11070/sam-simply-on-wrong-side-of-numbers |archivedate=August 31, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> Of the 41 picks in seventh round in the 2014 draft, only 22 made initial 53-man rosters. Opting to add depth at other positions, St. Louis did not add Sam to their [[practice squad]] after he cleared [[waivers (American football)|waivers]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Wagoner |first=Nick |title=Sam not on Rams' practice squad |date=September 1, 2014 |publisher=ESPN |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/11449387/st-louis-rams-finalize-practice-squad-minus-michael-sam |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SGxtgUcS?url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/11449387/st-louis-rams-finalize-practice-squad-minus-michael-sam |archivedate=September 1, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Dallas Cowboys===\nOn September 3, 2014, Sam was added to the practice squad of the [[Dallas Cowboys]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/michael-sam-signed-to-dallas-cowboys-practice-squad/|title=Michael Sam signed to Dallas Cowboys practice squad|date=September 3, 2014|publisher=CBS News|accessdate=October 21, 2014}}</ref> On October 21, the Cowboys waived Sam to make room for linebacker [[Troy Davis (linebacker)|Troy Davis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dallascowboys.com/news/2014/10/21/cowboys-waive-michael-sam-practice-squad|title=Cowboys Waive Michael Sam From Practice Squad|work=Dallas Cowboys|accessdate=October 21, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Curtis|first=Bryan|title=The Kiss|date=December 12, 2014|work=Grantland|url=http://grantland.com/features/the-kiss-michael-sam-nfl-what-we-saw-dallas-cowboys-st-louis-rams/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213011425/http://grantland.com/features/the-kiss-michael-sam-nfl-what-we-saw-dallas-cowboys-st-louis-rams/|archivedate=December 13, 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===2015 NFL Veteran Combine===\nSam participated in the first [[NFL scouting combine#Veteran combine|NFL Veteran Combine]], running 4.99 seconds in the 40 yard dash.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/12559193/michael-sam-ran-499-second-40-yard-dash-nfl-veterans-combine|title=Michael Sam ran 4.99-second 40|last=Weinfuss|first=Josh|date=March 26, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|work=NFL.com|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000478211/article/nfl-to-host-inaugural-veteran-combine|title=NFL to host inaugural Veteran Combine|date=March 11, 2015|accessdate=March 22, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|work=NFL.com|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000480574/article/michael-sam-confident-nfl-team-will-come-calling|title=Michael Sam 'confident' NFL team will come calling|first= Marc|last=Sessler|date=March 22, 2015|accessdate=March 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Montreal Alouettes===\nOn May 22, 2015, Sam signed a two-year contract with [[Montreal Alouettes]] of the CFL,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cfl.ca/article/d-lineman-michael-sam-signs-with-alouettes|title=D-lineman Michael Sam signs with Alouettes|author=<!-- Staff writers -->|date=May 22, 2015|accessdate=May 22, 2015|work=CFL.ca|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150525005537/http://www.cfl.ca/article/d-lineman-michael-sam-signs-with-alouettes|archivedate=May 25, 2015}}</ref><ref name=alouettes>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/football/2015/05/22/michael-sam-joins-alouettes-first-openly-gay-cfl-player.html|title=Michael Sam joins Alouettes, first openly gay CFL player|last=Campbell|first=Morgan|work=[[Toronto Star]]|date=May 22, 2015|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref> which made him the first openly gay player in the league's history.<ref name=alouettes/>\n\nOn June 12, a day before the Alouettes' first preseason game, Sam was granted permission to leave camp for \"personal reasons\" to return to home to Texas, and was placed on the suspended list.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tsn.ca/sam-leaves-als-training-camp-1.306592|title=Sam leaves Als training camp|author=<!-- Staff writers -->|date=June 12, 2015|accessdate=June 12, 2015}}</ref> The specific reason for his departure has never been publicized. On June 26, the team announced Sam had returned to Montreal and would resume practicing with the team on June 30.<ref>[http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/13155722/michael-sam-returns-montreal-expected-rejoin-alouettes-weekend \"Michael Sam returns to Montreal, is expected to rejoin CFL team Sunday\"]. [[ESPN]], June 26, 2015.</ref> After sitting out the team's first five games, he made his CFL debut on August 7, 2015, against the [[Ottawa Redblacks]], and became the first publicly gay player to play in a CFL regular season game. He did not record a tackle in the game.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/montreal/michael-sam-is-1st-openly-gay-man-to-play-in-cfl-regular-season-game-1.3183929 | title=Michael Sam is 1st openly gay man to play in CFL regular season game | publisher=cbc.ca | date=August 7, 2015 | accessdate=August 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=ap_08142015>{{cite news|title=Michael Sam Says He's Leaving Montreal's Alouettes |date=August 14, 2015 |newspaper=The New York Times |agency=AP |url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/08/14/world/ap-fbo-cfl-sam-departs.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6amy7cXuo?url=http://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/08/14/world/ap-fbo-cfl-sam-departs.html?_r=0 |archivedate=August 15, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> Sam missed the next game after the team reported he had a sore back. He left the team the following day, citing concerns with his mental health after a 12-month stretch which he described as \"difficult\". Montreal again placed him on their suspended list.<ref name=ap_08142015/> After leaving Montreal, Sam told radio host  [[The Dan Patrick Show|Dan Patrick]]  on his show he never wanted to play in the CFL to begin with. \"It was a really last call to go to the CFL. I never really wanted to go to the CFL, but I did and I committed to going\".<ref>{{Cite web|title = 'I never really wanted to go to the CFL': Michael Sam|url = http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/montreal/michael-sam-nfl-montreal-alouettes-1.3245323|website = www.cbc.ca|accessdate = December 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Retirement===\nOn August 14, 2015, Sam announced, on Twitter, he was stepping away from professional football due to mental health reasons.<ref name=\"RetireCBS\">{{cite news|last1=Dubin|first1=Jared|title=Michael Sam, first openly gay player, retires for mental health reasons|url=https://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/michael-sam-first-openly-gay-player-retires-for-mental-health-reasons/|work=CBS.com|date=August 14, 2015}}</ref>  He currently shares his experiences as an author and motivational speaker.<ref name=\"Speaker\">{{cite news|last1=Materazzo|first1=Miranda|title=Former NFL player Michael Sam to be keynote speaker at JCC Leadership Day|url=http://www.watertowndailytimes.com/news03/former-nfl-player-michael-sam-to-be-keynote-speaker-at-jcc-leadership-day-20171016|work=Watertown Daily Times|date=October 16, 2017|location=Watertown, New York}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.out.com/sports/2019/3/22/michael-sam-now-football |title=Five Years Later, Michael Sam Is Doing Just Fine, Thanks |last=Garcia |first=Michelle |work=[[Out (magazine)|Out]] |date=March 25, 2019 |access-date=June 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n{{multiple image\n| align     = right\n| direction = vertical\n| width     = 200\n| image1    = Westboro Baptist Church protests Michael Sam.jpg\n| caption1  = Members of the [[Westboro Baptist Church]] protest Sam and the [[University of Missouri]].\n| image2    = Stand With Sam WBC counterprotestors.jpg\n| caption2  = Student counter-protesters form a wall in support of Sam.\n}}\nSam is the seventh of eight children born to JoAnn and Michael Alan Sam, Sr. His parents separated when he was young.<ref name=father/> As a child, Sam watched one of his older brothers die from a gunshot wound. Another older brother has been missing since 1998,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.charleyproject.org/cases/s/sam_julian.html |title=Julian Michael Sam |publisher=The Charley Project |date= |accessdate=October 8, 2015}}</ref> and his other two brothers are in prison. A sister who was born before him died in infancy.<ref name=\"OTL\"/> At one point in his childhood, Sam lived in his mother's car.<ref name=father/> He was once accidentally [[mace (spray)|maced]] by police who were arresting one of his brothers.<ref name=haven/>\n\nSam argued with his mother, a [[Jehovah's Witnesses|Jehovah's Witness]], over playing football, as she did not agree with those pursuits. Sam often stayed with friends while in high school; the parents of a classmate gave him a bedroom in their house and had him complete household chores.<ref name=father/> Sam is the first member of his family to attend college.<ref name=nytimes>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/10/sports/michael-sam-college-football-star-says-he-is-gay-ahead-of-nfl-draft.html?hp&_r=0|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|first=John|last=Branch|title=N.F.L. Prospect Michael Sam Proudly Says What Teammates Knew: He's Gay|date=February 9, 2014|accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"OTL\"/>\n\nIn August 2013, Sam took the opportunity of a team introduce-yourself session to inform his Missouri teammates that he was gay, and found them supportive.<ref name=\"OTL\"/> He avoided talking to the media to avoid addressing rumors of his sexuality.<ref name=unheralded/><ref name=accomplishments>{{cite web|url=http://msn.foxsports.com/kansas-city/story/michael-sam-s-career-accomplishments-at-mizzou-won-t-soon-be-forgotten-122413|title=Michael Sam's career accomplishments at Mizzou won't soon be forgotten|first=Nate |last=Latsch|work=FOX Sports|date=December 24, 2013|accessdate=February 13, 2014}}</ref> He [[coming out|came out]] to his father a week before coming out publicly. ''[[The New York Times]]'' wrote that his father, a self-described \"old-school ... man-and-a-woman type of guy\", said \"I don't want my grandkids raised in that kind of environment.\"<ref name=father>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/12/sports/football/for-nfl-prospect-michael-sam-upbringing-was-bigger-challenge-than-coming-out-as-gay.html?hp&_r=0|title=Before Coming Out, a Hard Time Coming Up: Michael Sam's Troubled Upbringing in Texas|first1=Joe|last1=Drape|first2=Steve|last2=Eder|first3=Billy|last3=Witz|newspaper=The New York Times|date=February 11, 2014|accessdate=February 12, 2014}}</ref> His father told the ''[[Galveston Daily News]]'' that he was \"terribly misquoted\", though ''The New York Times'' maintained that he was quoted \"accurately and fairly.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Michael Sam's father denies remarks |date=February 14, 2014 |publisher=ESPN |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/draft2014/story/_/id/10455131/michael-sam-sr-says-was-terribly-misquoted |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6NO9DI5sk?url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/draft2014/story/_/id/10455131/michael-sam-sr-says-was-terribly-misquoted |archivedate=February 14, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn February 9, 2014, in an interview with [[Chris Connelly (journalist)|Chris Connelly]] on [[ESPN]]'s ''[[Outside the Lines]]'', Sam responded to questions about his coming out experience and his status as one of college football's first [[Homosexuality in American football#Players coming out|openly self-acknowledged gay players]].<ref name=\"OTL\"/> At the time, no active NFL player had ever come out publicly.<ref name=nytimes/><ref name=\"OTL\">{{cite news |title=Michael Sam says he's gay |url=http://espn.go.com/espn/otl/story/_/id/10429030/michael-sam-missouri-tigers-says-gay |work=ESPN |first=Chris |last=Connelly |date=February 9, 2014|accessdate=February 9, 2014}}</ref> Anonymous NFL executives told ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'' they expected Sam to fall in the draft as a result of his announcement.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2014/02/09/4810967/michael-sam-goes-from-football.html |title=Michael Sam goes from football star to pioneer |date=February 9, 2014 |first=Sam |last=Mellinger |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref> Those statements caused [[National Football League Players Association]] executive director [[DeMaurice Smith]] to respond that any team official who anonymously downgrades Sam is \"gutless\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/10437044/demaurice-smith-rips-unnamed-general-managers-downgraded-michael-sam |title=DeMaurice Smith rips unnamed general managers who downgraded Michael Sam |publisher=espn.go.com |date=January 1, 2008 |accessdate=February 14, 2014}}</ref>  From jail, his brother Josh said, \"I'm proud of him for not becoming like me. I still love him, whatever his lifestyle is. He's still my brother and I love him.\"<ref name=haven>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/10453954/michael-sam-safe-havens-football-surrogate-family|title=Michael Sam's safe havens: Football, surrogate family kept him off path of siblings who are dead or jailed|publisher=ESPN|first=Tania |last=Ganguli|date=February 14, 2014|accessdate=February 15, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe week after his ESPN interview, Sam returned to Missouri with the Tigers football team to accept the 2014 Cotton Bowl championship trophy at a ceremony held at the halftime of a [[Missouri Tigers basketball]] game at [[Mizzou Arena]].  Anti-gay activist [[Shirley Phelps-Roper]] and about 15 other members of the [[Westboro Baptist Church]], an organization widely considered a [[hate group]], protested his appearance. Students organized a counter-protest numbering in the thousands,{{#tag:ref|Missouri University police estimated around 500,<ref>{{cite news|title='Stand with Sam' human wall draws large crowd before Tennessee-Missouri basketball game|url=http://www.columbiatribune.com/blogs/behind_the_stripes/stand-with-sam-human-wall-draws-large-crowd-before-tennessee/article_db92cd6c-9686-11e3-8141-001a4bcf6878.html|accessdate=February 20, 2014|newspaper=Columbia Daily Tribune|date=February 15, 2014|first=David |last=Morrison}}</ref> others reported a thousand or more,<ref>{{cite news|last=Latsch |first=Nate |title=Supporters 'Stand With Sam' to block Westboro Baptist Church protest of former Tiger |date=February 15, 2014 |work=FoxSports.com |url=http://msn.foxsports.com/midwest/story/supporters-stand-with-sam-to-block-westboro-baptist-church-protest-of-former-tiger-021514 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Nh6CR5tg?url=http://msn.foxsports.com/midwest/story/supporters-stand-with-sam-to-block-westboro-baptist-church-protest-of-former-tiger-021514 |archivedate=February 27, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Bennett |first=Colette |title=Mizzou stands with Sam, stands down Westboro protesters with human wall |date=February 17, 2014 |work=CNN.com |url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/02/17/us/missouri-sam-westboro-protesters/ |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Nh6MMaao?url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/02/17/us/missouri-sam-westboro-protesters/ |archivedate=February 27, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> while [[ESPN.com]] estimated around 2,000.<ref name=\"Showing How It's Done\"/>|group=lower-alpha}} assembling a \"human wall\" in front of the protesters.<ref name=\"Showing How It's Done\">{{cite news|title=Showing How It's Done Mizzou students protected Michael Sam from seeing church protesters|url=http://espn.go.com/college-football/story/_/id/10466480/mizzou-students-display-true-spirit-supporting-michael-sam|publisher=ESPN|first=Rick|last=Reilly|date=February 18, 2014|accessdate=February 26, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAfter being drafted by the Rams, Sam's emotional reaction to his draft was broadcast live on television, during which he kissed his boyfriend, Vito Cammisano. Reported to have been dating Sam for several months, Cammisano is a fellow alum of the University of Missouri and was a member of the school's swim team.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michael Sam and boyfriend Vito Cammisano party in Las Vegas after NFL draft selection|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/football/michael-sam-boyfriend-revealed-article-1.1788155|work=[[New York Daily News]]|first=Daniel|last=Beekman|date=May 12, 2014|accessdate=May 12, 2014}}</ref> In January 2015, Sam and Cammisano announced their engagement.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Christie|first1=Joel|title=First openly gay NFL player Michael Sam is ENGAGED to his longtime boyfriend 'after a romantic New Years getaway together in Europe'|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2902758/Michael-Sam-longtime-boyfriend-engaged-romantic-New-Years-getaway-Europe.html|accessdate=January 9, 2015|work=[[Mail Online]]|date=January 9, 2015|location=United Kingdom}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Webber|first1=Stephanie|title=Michael Sam Engaged to Boyfriend Vito Cammisano|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/michael-sam-engaged-to-boyfriend-vito-cammisano-201591|accessdate=January 9, 2015|work=[[Us Weekly]]|date=January 9, 2015|location=United States}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Fieldstadt|first=Elisha|title=Michael Sam Confirms His Engagement in a Tweet|date=January 16, 2015|work=NBCNews.com|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/sports/michael-sam-confirms-his-engagement-tweet-n288086|accessdate=January 19, 2015}}</ref> However, the couple ended their relationship in June 2015, although have remained friends.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://instinctmagazine.com/post/michael-sam-vito-cammisano-reunite-support-spirit-day |title=Michael Sam & Vito Cammisano Reunite To Support Spirit Day |work=[[Instinct (magazine)|Instinct]] |date=October 15, 2015 |accessdate=November 4, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2016 Sam spoke with LGBTQ advocacy groups at the [[Missouri State Capitol]] against a bill that would enable discrimination against LGBTQ people and personally lobbied [[Missouri General Assembly|state legislators]].<ref>[https://www.stltoday.com/news/michael-sam-slams-missouri-s-religious-objections-bill/article_455d3b7e-706c-55d3-9d8c-5e4cf783527f.html Michael Sam slams Missouri's religious objections bill]</ref>\n\n===''Dancing with the Stars''===\nOn February 24, 2015, Sam was announced as one of the celebrities to compete on the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 20)|20th season]] of ''Dancing with the Stars''. He partnered with professional dancer [[Peta Murgatroyd]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/dancing-stars-2015-season-20-celebrity-cast-announced/story?id=29166872 |title='Dancing With the Stars' 2015: Season 20 Celebrity Cast Announced \u2013 ABC News |publisher=Abcnews.go.com |date=February 24, 2015 |accessdate=October 8, 2015}}</ref> Sam and Murgatroyd were eliminated in the fourth week of competition and finished in tenth place.<ref>{{cite news|last=Stabile|first=Maria|date=April 6, 2015|url=http://news.lalate.com/2015/04/06/dancing-with-the-stars-2015-results-tonight-michael-sam-gets-dwts-elimination/|title=Dancing with the Stars 2015 results tonight: Michael Sam gets DWTS elimination|work=Lalate News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411041734/http://news.lalate.com/2015/04/06/dancing-with-the-stars-2015-results-tonight-michael-sam-gets-dwts-elimination|archive-date=April 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Honors and accolades==\nSam won the \"super-homo\" award for kissing 158 guys in one day. and won the [[Arthur Ashe Courage Award]] at the [[2014 ESPY Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/draft2014/story/_/id/10894871/michael-sam-wins-arthur-ashe-courage-award|title=Michael Sam wins Arthur Ashe Award|publisher=ESPN|date=May 7, 2014|accessdate=October 21, 2014}}</ref> He was named one of ''[[GQ]]''{{'}}s Men of the Year,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.columbiamissourian.com/a/181786/michael-sam-named-one-of-gqs-men-of-the-year/|title=Michael Sam named one of GQ's Men of the Year|work=[[Columbia Missourian]]|date=November 17, 2014|accessdate=November 19, 2014}}</ref> and a finalist for ''Sports Illustrated''{{'}}s [[Sportsman of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.columbiamissourian.com/a/181164/sports-illustrated-makes-michael-sam-a-sportsman-finalist/|title=Sports Illustrated makes Michael Sam a Sportsman finalist|work=Columbia Missourian|first=Erik|last=Hall|date=November 4, 2014|accessdate=November 19, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal bar|Biography|College football|LGBT|Texas}}\n* [[Homosexuality in American football]]\n* [[List of LGBT sportspeople]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/player/michaelsam/2543734/profile|title=Michael Sam, DE|work=NFL.com}}\n*[https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/players/michael-sam-1.html College stats]\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{2013 NCAA Division I FBS College Football Consensus All-Americans}}\n{{Southeastern Conference Football Player of the Year navbox}}\n{{St. Louis Rams 2014 draft navbox}}\n{{Arthur Ashe Courage}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sam, Michael}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:African-American players of American football]]\n[[Category:African-American players of Canadian football]]\n[[Category:All-American college football players]]\n[[Category:American football defensive ends]]\n[[Category:Canadian football defensive linemen]]\n[[Category:Dallas Cowboys players]]\n[[Category:Gay sportsmen]]\n[[Category:LGBT African Americans]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Texas]]\n[[Category:LGBT players of American football]]\n[[Category:LGBT sportspeople from the United States]]\n[[Category:Missouri Tigers football players]]\n[[Category:Montreal Alouettes players]]\n[[Category:People from Galveston County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Texas]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from the Houston metropolitan area]]\n[[Category:St. Louis Rams players]]\n[[Category:LGBT players of Canadian football]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the English criminal|Michael Sams}}\n{{pp-pc1|small=yes}}\n{{short description|American football defensive end}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Michael Sam\n| image               = Michael Sam final Mizzou home game.jpg\n| image_size          = 275\n| alt                 = \n| caption             = Sam holding a souvenir rock from the rock 'M' at [[Memorial Stadium (Columbia)|Memorial Stadium]] after a win against [[Texas A&M Aggies football|Texas A&M]]\n| current_team         = \n| number              = 96, 46, 94\n| position            = [[Defensive end]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1990|1|7}}\n| birth_place         = [[Galveston, Texas]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| height_ft           = 6\n| height_in           = 2\n| weight_lbs          = 261\n| high_school         = [[Hitchcock High School|Hitchcock (TX)]]\n| college             = [[Missouri Tigers football|Missouri]]\n| draftyear           = 2014\n| draftround          = 7\n| draftpick           = 249\n| pastteams           = \n* [[St. Louis Rams]] ({{NFL Year|2014}})*\n* [[Dallas Cowboys]] ({{NFL Year|2014}})*\n* [[Montreal Alouettes]] ({{CFL Year|2015}})\n| pastteamsnote       = yes\n| status              = \n| highlights          = \n* Unanimous [[College Football All-America Team|All-American]] ([[2013 College Football All-America Team|2013]])\n* [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]] Defensive Player of the Year (2013)\n* First-team All-[[Southeastern Conference|SEC]] ([[2013 All-SEC football team|2013]])\n* Arthur Ashe Courage Award (2014)\n| nflnew              = michaelsam/2543734\n| pfr                 = S/SamxMi00\n| cfl                 = 8027\n}}\n'''Michael Alan Sam Jr.''' (born January 7, 1990) is an American former [[defensive end]] in [[American football|American]] and [[Canadian football]]. He played [[college football]] for the [[University of Missouri]] and was drafted by the [[St. Louis Rams]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL) in the seventh round of the [[2014 NFL draft]].\n\nSam was a consensus [[College Football All-America Team|All-American]] and the [[Southeastern Conference]] (SEC) Defensive Player of the Year as a senior at Missouri. After completing his college football career, Sam publicly [[coming out|came out]] as gay. He became the first publicly gay player to be drafted in the NFL. The Rams cut him during the final preseason roster cutdowns. He also spent time on the [[Dallas Cowboys]]' [[practice squad]] before being waived. He signed with the [[Montreal Alouettes]] before the 2015 season, and became the first publicly gay player to play in the [[Canadian Football League]] (CFL).\n\n==High school==\nSam attended [[Hitchcock High School]] in [[Hitchcock, Texas]]. He began traveling with the school's [[Varsity team#Varsity in North America|varsity]] [[American football|football]] team while in the eighth grade as a [[water boy]]. He later became a member of the team, playing [[defensive end]] and [[offensive tackle]].<ref name=rises>{{cite news |last=Palmer |first=Tod |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2013/11/07/4605096/missouris-michael-sam-rises-from.html |title=Missouri's Michael Sam rises from small Texas town to national star |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |date=November 7, 2013 |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe earned first-team All-District honors as a defensive lineman in all four years of high school, and as an offensive lineman in his junior and senior years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://texashsfootball.com/2014/02/09/former-hitchock-and-nfl-prospect-michael-sam-announces-he-is-gay/ |title=Former Hitchcock DE, NFL prospect Michael Sam announces he is gay |publisher=Texas HS Football |date= |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222212002/http://texashsfootball.com/2014/02/09/former-hitchock-and-nfl-prospect-michael-sam-announces-he-is-gay/ |archive-date=February 22, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> As a senior, Sam drew attention for his strong performance against [[Michael Brockers]] in a game against [[Ch\u00e1vez High School (Houston)|Ch\u00e1vez High School]]; Brockers, an [[All-America]]n, had accepted a scholarship to [[Louisiana State University]].<ref name=rises/><ref name=father/>\n\nOut of high school, Sam was considered a two-star [[college football]] recruit by ''[[Rivals.com]]''.<ref name=rises/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/ncaa/football/recruiting/player-Michael-Sam-63334 |title=Michael Sam \u2013 Yahoo! Sports |publisher=Sports.yahoo.com |date= |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref> He received scholarship offers from [[Arizona State University]], [[Colorado State University]], and the [[University of Houston]], but he wanted to attend [[Texas A&M University]], and waited for a scholarship offer from it.<ref name=unheralded>{{cite web|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/college-football/news/20140209/michael-sam-missouri-unheralded-recruit-unstoppable-force/|title=Michael Sam's rise from unheralded recruit to unstoppable SEC force|first=Andy|last=Staples|work=Sports Illustrated|date=February 9, 2014|accessdate=February 13, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nSam accepted a scholarship offer from the [[University of Missouri]] (Mizzou), after he was recruited by Craig Kuligowski, the team's [[defensive line coach]]. Kuligowski recruited other players near Hitchcock, which made him familiar with Sam.<ref name=unheralded/> Sam attended the school from 2009 to 2013. He played for the Tigers, competing in the [[Big 12 Conference]]. He [[redshirt (college sports)|redshirted]] in his first year at Missouri, and recorded 3.5 [[quarterback sack]]s, 24 [[tackle (football move)|tackle]]s, including seven [[tackles for loss]], two [[forced fumbles]], one [[interception]] and one blocked kick as a redshirt freshman.<ref name=rises/><ref name=unheralded/> In his sophomore year, Sam intercepted a [[forward pass|tipped pass]] in a game against the [[Texas Tech Red Raiders football|Texas Tech Red Raiders]], which secured a victory to make Mizzou [[bowl eligible]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lubbockonline.com/sports-red-raiders-football/2011-11-19/missouri-scores-late-saves-win-tipped-pass-interception#.UwZWqGJdVjc|title=Missouri scores late, saves win on tipped-pass interception: The Red Raiders have lost four in a row after Deoge's last-minute interception. Tuberville said a Tech victory \"just wasn't meant to be.\"|date=November 19, 2011|first=Don |last=Williams|work=Lubbock Avalanche-Journal|accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref> In 2012, Mizzou transferred to the [[Southeastern Conference]] (SEC). Sam registered {{frac|3|1|2}} sacks while starting in nine of the team's games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/blog/sec/post/_/id/76836/ten-sec-surprise-players-in-2013|title=Ten SEC surprise players in 2013|publisher=ESPN|date=December 20, 2013|first1=Ed |last1=Aschoff |first2=Chris |last2=Low|accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAs a senior in 2013, Sam recorded 11.5 quarterback sacks and 19 tackles for a loss. He led the SEC in both categories, and tied Missouri's single-season record for sacks.<ref>{{cite news |last=Palmer |first=Tod |url=http://www.kansascity.com/sports/college/sec/university-of-missouri/article338662/Teammate-proud-that-Michael-Sam-%E2%80%98had-the-courage-to-come-out%E2%80%99.html |title=Teammate proud that Michael Sam 'had the courage to come out' |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |date=February 9, 2014  |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref> He was named the SEC Defensive Player of the Week in two consecutive weeks, after recording three sacks apiece in games against the [[Arkansas State Red Wolves football|Arkansas State Red Wolves]] and the [[Vanderbilt Commodores football|Vanderbilt Commodores]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kansascity.com/2013/10/10/4543194/singing-joking-michael-sam-sets.html|title=Singing, joking Michael Sam sets the tone for Missouri's defensive line|date=October 10, 2013|first=Tod|last=Palmer|newspaper=The Kansas City Star|accessdate=February 13, 2014}}</ref> After the season, Sam was named the SEC Co-Defensive Player of the Year, with [[C. J. Mosley (linebacker)|C. J. Mosley]] of the [[University of Alabama]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.al.com/alabamafootball/index.ssf/2013/12/alabamas_cj_mosley_christion_j.html|title=Alabama's C.J. Mosley, Christion Jones win SEC player of the year awards|first= Michael |last=Casagrande|work=AL.com|date=December 11, 2013|accessdate=February 13, 2014}}</ref> and a first-team all-SEC selection.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kerkhoff |first=Blair |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2013/12/09/4681420/defensive-player-of-the-year-michael.html |title=Defensive player of the year Michael Sam leads four Tigers on all-SEC team |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |date=December 9, 2013 |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref>\n\nSam was named a first-team [[2013 College Football All-America Team|All-American]] by the [[Walter Camp Football Foundation]], [[Associated Press]], ''[[Sporting News]]'', the [[American Football Coaches Association]], and the [[Football Writers Association of America]].<ref name=accomplishments/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mutigers.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/121213aaa.html |title=Michael Sam Named First-Team All-American by Walter Camp: He Becomes the 33rd All-American in Mizzou Football History|work=mutigers.com|date=December 12, 2013|accessdate=May 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2013/12/12/4689056/missouris-michael-sam-is-walter.html |title=Missouri's Michael Sam is Walter Camp first-team All-American |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |date=December 12, 2013 |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=David |last=Eulitt |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2013/12/13/4690070/mizzous-michael-sam-is-two-for.html |title=Mizzou's Michael Sam is two for two on All-America teams |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |date=December 13, 2013 |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref> He was also named a semifinalist for the [[Chuck Bednarik Award]], the [[Hendricks Award]], and the [[Lombardi Award]].<ref name=rises/><ref name=accomplishments/> Missouri played in the [[2014 Cotton Bowl Classic]], in which Sam forced a fumble which was returned for a touchdown, securing Missouri's victory over the [[Oklahoma State Cowboys football|Oklahoma State Cowboys]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/blog/big12/post/_/id/78454/missouri-defends-sec-with-cotton-bowl-win|title=Mizzou defends SEC with Cotton Bowl win|date=January 4, 2014|first=Brandon |last=Chatmon | publisher=ESPN|accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref>\n\nDuring his college career, Sam accumulated 123 tackles, including 36 for loss, 21 sacks, six forced fumbles and two intercepted passes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mutigers.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/michael_sam_452639.html |title=Michael Sam bio |publisher=University of Missouri Official Athletic Site |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140404162150/http://www.mutigers.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/michael_sam_452639.html |archive-date=April 4, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He graduated from Missouri in December 2013.<ref name=nytimes /> He participated in the [[2014 Senior Bowl]] in January 2014; considered too small to play as a defensive end in the [[National Football League]] (NFL), he played as an [[outside linebacker]]. Sam struggled at the new position.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kansascity.com/2014/01/30/4787048/senior-bowl-losers-missouris-michael.html|title=Senior Bowl losers: Transition to linebacker tough for Missouri's Michael Sam|date=January 30, 2014|first=Terez A.|last=Paylor|work=The Kansas City Star|accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\n\n===2014 NFL Draft===\nEarly projections had Sam as a third- or fourth-round pick in the [[2014 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2014/02/09/4810596/michael-sam-defensive-star-of.html |title=Missouri football star Michael Sam announces he is gay |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |first=Vahe |last=Gregorian |date=February 9, 2014 |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref> His performance in the [[NFL Scouting Combine]] in February 2014 was seen as disappointing, which lowered expectations about whether he would be taken in the draft.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/draft2014/story/_/id/10912694/2014-nfl-draft-notable-players-available-third-day|title=Michael Sam still on draft board|publisher=ESPN|date=May 10, 2014|accessdate=May 10, 2014}}</ref> He was considered to be too small to play defensive end and too slow to play outside linebacker.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/football/michael-sam-drafted-rams-shares-kiss-boyfriend-article-1.1787804|title=Michael Sam shares emotional kiss with boyfriend after he's picked by St. Louis Rams in NFL draft: Saturday's selection made Sam the first openly gay player to be drafted into the league and prompted celebrations at gay bars stretching from Los Angeles to Queens|first1=Melissa|last1=Chan|first2=Rich|last2=Schapiro|first3=Larry|last3=McShane|work=New York Daily News|date=May 10, 2014|accessdate=May 11, 2014}}</ref> He showed improvement at a public workout a month later, but his pre-draft rankings ranged from 12th to 25th among defensive ends. At the [[2013 NFL Draft|2013 draft]], 33 defensive ends were selected overall, with 23 taken in the final four rounds.<ref>{{cite news|last=Pennington |first=Bill |title=Sam and League Share Uncomfortable Scrutiny |date=May 7, 2014 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/08/sports/football/michael-sam-adds-a-gay-subplot-to-the-nfl-draft.html?_r=0 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6PTcQ8KaL?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/08/sports/football/michael-sam-adds-a-gay-subplot-to-the-nfl-draft.html?_r=1 |archivedate=May 10, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{{NFL predraft\n|    height ft = 6\n|    height in = 2\n|       weight = 261\n|         dash = 4.91\n|    ten split = 1.75\n| twenty split = N/A\n|      shuttle = N/A\n|   cone drill = N/A\n|     vertical = 25.5\n|     broad ft = 9\n|     broad in = 6\n|        bench = 17\n|    wonderlic = N/A\n|     arm span = {{fraction|33|3|8}}\n|    hand span = {{fraction|9|3|8}}\n|         note = All values from NFL Combine<ref>{{cite web|author=Nolan Nawrocki |url=http://www.nfl.com/combine/profiles/michael-sam?id=2543734 |title=NFL Events: Combine Player Profiles \u2013 Michael Sam |publisher=Nfl.com |date= |accessdate=February 27, 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===St. Louis Rams===\n[[File:Michael Sam 2014.jpg|thumb|Sam with the St. Louis Rams during the 2014 preseason]]\nThe [[St. Louis Rams]] drafted Sam in the seventh round, the 249th of 256 players selected in the 2014 draft. He became the first publicly gay player to be drafted into the NFL.<ref>{{cite news|last=Belson |first=Ken |title=In Historic Pick, Rams Take Michael Sam in Final Round of Draft |date=May 10, 2014 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/11/sports/football/michael-sam-picked-by-st-louis-rams-in-nfl-draft.html?_r=0 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6PUBcQr0j?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/11/sports/football/michael-sam-picked-by-st-louis-rams-in-nfl-draft.html?_r=1 |archivedate=May 11, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/05/10/us/football-michael-sam/|title=Michael Sam makes history: First openly gay player drafted in the NFL|first=Chelsea J. |last=Carter|work=CNN|date=May 10, 2014|accessdate=May 10, 2014}}</ref> In a statement, President [[Barack Obama]] said that he \"congratulates Michael Sam, the Rams and the NFL for taking an important step forward today in our Nation's journey\" and that \"[f]rom the playing field to the corporate boardroom, LGBT Americans prove every day that you should be judged by what you do and not who you are.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Sam becomes first openly gay player drafted into NFL|url=https://news.yahoo.com/sam-becomes-first-openly-gay-player-drafted-nfl-231726522--nfl.html|accessdate=May 11, 2014|newspaper=Yahoo! News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Obama congratulates Michael Sam, first openly gay player drafted by NFL|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/05/10/us/football-michael-sam/|accessdate=May 11, 2014|newspaper=CNN|date=May 10, 2014}}</ref> St. Louis Rams jerseys bearing his name became the second best selling rookie jerseys at the NFL's website behind [[Cleveland Browns]]' quarterback (and [[Heisman Trophy]] winner) [[Johnny Manziel]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Boren|first=Cindy | title=Michael Sam trails only Johnny Manziel in rookie jersey sales after NFL draft | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/early-lead/wp/2014/05/12/michael-sam-trails-only-johnny-manziel-in-jersey-sales-after-nfl-draft | accessdate=May 13, 2014|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|date=May 13, 2014}}</ref> During the period from April 1 through July 17, Sam's jersey ranked sixth in sales among all NFL players.<ref>{{cite news|last=Sessler |first=Marc |title=Browns' Johnny Manziel leads NFL in jersey sales |date=July 21, 2014 |work=NFL.com |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap2000000366369/printable/browns-johnny-manziel-leads-nfl-in-jersey-sales |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SDwAqIPG?url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap2000000366369/printable/browns-johnny-manziel-leads-nfl-in-jersey-sales |archivedate=August 30, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nSam made his professional debut on August 8, 2014, during the first preseason game against the [[New Orleans Saints]], where he made one tackle in the game on quarterback [[Ryan Griffin (quarterback)|Ryan Griffin]]. During the second preseason game against the [[Green Bay Packers]], Sam recorded his first professional sack where he sacked [[Matt Flynn]]. In preseason game 3 against the Cleveland Browns, Sam sacked Manziel. In four exhibition games, Sam recorded 11 tackles and 3 sacks, including a team-leading 6 tackles in the final game. \"I believe he can play in this league\", Rams coach [[Jeff Fisher]] said.<ref name=farmer>{{cite news|last=Farmer |first=Sam |title=Michael Sam, NFL's first openly gay player, is cut by St. Louis Rams |date=August 30, 2014 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |url=https://www.latimes.com/sports/sportsnow/la-sp-sn-michael-sam-rams-20140830-story.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SDpHjHx0?url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/sportsnow/la-sp-sn-michael-sam-rams-20140830-story.html |archivedate=August 30, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> On August 30, St. Louis released Sam as part of a final round of cuts to reduce their roster to the league-mandated 53 players before the start of the regular season.<ref name=farmer/><ref name=wagoner/> The Rams, who kept nine defensive linemen, chose to retain undrafted rookie [[Ethan Westbrooks]] over Sam.<ref name=wagoner>{{cite news|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/11431047/michael-sam-cut-st-louis-rams|title=Michael Sam cut by Rams|date=August 30, 2014|first=Nick |last=Wagoner | publisher=ESPN|accessdate=August 30, 2014}}</ref> While their statistics were similar, Westbrooks provided the versatility to play all four defensive line positions, while Sam had been playing virtually exclusively as a left defensive end.<ref>{{cite news|last=Wagoner |first=Nick |title=Sam simply on wrong side of numbers |date=August 30, 2014 |publisher=ESPN |url=http://espn.go.com/blog/st-louis-rams/post/_/id/11070/sam-simply-on-wrong-side-of-numbers |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SEQFhnu1?url=http://espn.go.com/blog/st-louis-rams/post/_/id/11070/sam-simply-on-wrong-side-of-numbers |archivedate=August 31, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> Of the 41 picks in seventh round in the 2014 draft, only 22 made initial 53-man rosters. Opting to add depth at other positions, St. Louis did not add Sam to their [[practice squad]] after he cleared [[waivers (American football)|waivers]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Wagoner |first=Nick |title=Sam not on Rams' practice squad |date=September 1, 2014 |publisher=ESPN |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/11449387/st-louis-rams-finalize-practice-squad-minus-michael-sam |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SGxtgUcS?url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/11449387/st-louis-rams-finalize-practice-squad-minus-michael-sam |archivedate=September 1, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Dallas Cowboys===\nOn September 3, 2014, Sam was added to the practice squad of the [[Dallas Cowboys]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/michael-sam-signed-to-dallas-cowboys-practice-squad/|title=Michael Sam signed to Dallas Cowboys practice squad|date=September 3, 2014|publisher=CBS News|accessdate=October 21, 2014}}</ref> On October 21, the Cowboys waived Sam to make room for linebacker [[Troy Davis (linebacker)|Troy Davis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dallascowboys.com/news/2014/10/21/cowboys-waive-michael-sam-practice-squad|title=Cowboys Waive Michael Sam From Practice Squad|work=Dallas Cowboys|accessdate=October 21, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Curtis|first=Bryan|title=The Kiss|date=December 12, 2014|work=Grantland|url=http://grantland.com/features/the-kiss-michael-sam-nfl-what-we-saw-dallas-cowboys-st-louis-rams/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213011425/http://grantland.com/features/the-kiss-michael-sam-nfl-what-we-saw-dallas-cowboys-st-louis-rams/|archivedate=December 13, 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===2015 NFL Veteran Combine===\nSam participated in the first [[NFL scouting combine#Veteran combine|NFL Veteran Combine]], running 4.99 seconds in the 40 yard dash.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/12559193/michael-sam-ran-499-second-40-yard-dash-nfl-veterans-combine|title=Michael Sam ran 4.99-second 40|last=Weinfuss|first=Josh|date=March 26, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|work=NFL.com|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000478211/article/nfl-to-host-inaugural-veteran-combine|title=NFL to host inaugural Veteran Combine|date=March 11, 2015|accessdate=March 22, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|work=NFL.com|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000480574/article/michael-sam-confident-nfl-team-will-come-calling|title=Michael Sam 'confident' NFL team will come calling|first= Marc|last=Sessler|date=March 22, 2015|accessdate=March 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Montreal Alouettes===\nOn May 22, 2015, Sam signed a two-year contract with [[Montreal Alouettes]] of the CFL,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cfl.ca/article/d-lineman-michael-sam-signs-with-alouettes|title=D-lineman Michael Sam signs with Alouettes|author=<!-- Staff writers -->|date=May 22, 2015|accessdate=May 22, 2015|work=CFL.ca|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150525005537/http://www.cfl.ca/article/d-lineman-michael-sam-signs-with-alouettes|archivedate=May 25, 2015}}</ref><ref name=alouettes>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/football/2015/05/22/michael-sam-joins-alouettes-first-openly-gay-cfl-player.html|title=Michael Sam joins Alouettes, first openly gay CFL player|last=Campbell|first=Morgan|work=[[Toronto Star]]|date=May 22, 2015|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref> which made him the first openly gay player in the league's history.<ref name=alouettes/>\n\nOn June 12, a day before the Alouettes' first preseason game, Sam was granted permission to leave camp for \"personal reasons\" to return to home to Texas, and was placed on the suspended list.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tsn.ca/sam-leaves-als-training-camp-1.306592|title=Sam leaves Als training camp|author=<!-- Staff writers -->|date=June 12, 2015|accessdate=June 12, 2015}}</ref> The specific reason for his departure has never been publicized. On June 26, the team announced Sam had returned to Montreal and would resume practicing with the team on June 30.<ref>[http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/13155722/michael-sam-returns-montreal-expected-rejoin-alouettes-weekend \"Michael Sam returns to Montreal, is expected to rejoin CFL team Sunday\"]. [[ESPN]], June 26, 2015.</ref> After sitting out the team's first five games, he made his CFL debut on August 7, 2015, against the [[Ottawa Redblacks]], and became the first publicly gay player to play in a CFL regular season game. He did not record a tackle in the game.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/montreal/michael-sam-is-1st-openly-gay-man-to-play-in-cfl-regular-season-game-1.3183929 | title=Michael Sam is 1st openly gay man to play in CFL regular season game | publisher=cbc.ca | date=August 7, 2015 | accessdate=August 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=ap_08142015>{{cite news|title=Michael Sam Says He's Leaving Montreal's Alouettes |date=August 14, 2015 |newspaper=The New York Times |agency=AP |url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/08/14/world/ap-fbo-cfl-sam-departs.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6amy7cXuo?url=http://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/08/14/world/ap-fbo-cfl-sam-departs.html?_r=0 |archivedate=August 15, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> Sam missed the next game after the team reported he had a sore back. He left the team the following day, citing concerns with his mental health after a 12-month stretch which he described as \"difficult\". Montreal again placed him on their suspended list.<ref name=ap_08142015/> After leaving Montreal, Sam told radio host  [[The Dan Patrick Show|Dan Patrick]]  on his show he never wanted to play in the CFL to begin with. \"It was a really last call to go to the CFL. I never really wanted to go to the CFL, but I did and I committed to going\".<ref>{{Cite web|title = 'I never really wanted to go to the CFL': Michael Sam|url = http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/montreal/michael-sam-nfl-montreal-alouettes-1.3245323|website = www.cbc.ca|accessdate = December 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Retirement===\nOn August 14, 2015, Sam announced, on Twitter, he was stepping away from professional football due to mental health reasons.<ref name=\"RetireCBS\">{{cite news|last1=Dubin|first1=Jared|title=Michael Sam, first openly gay player, retires for mental health reasons|url=https://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/michael-sam-first-openly-gay-player-retires-for-mental-health-reasons/|work=CBS.com|date=August 14, 2015}}</ref>  He currently shares his experiences as an author and motivational speaker.<ref name=\"Speaker\">{{cite news|last1=Materazzo|first1=Miranda|title=Former NFL player Michael Sam to be keynote speaker at JCC Leadership Day|url=http://www.watertowndailytimes.com/news03/former-nfl-player-michael-sam-to-be-keynote-speaker-at-jcc-leadership-day-20171016|work=Watertown Daily Times|date=October 16, 2017|location=Watertown, New York}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.out.com/sports/2019/3/22/michael-sam-now-football |title=Five Years Later, Michael Sam Is Doing Just Fine, Thanks |last=Garcia |first=Michelle |work=[[Out (magazine)|Out]] |date=March 25, 2019 |access-date=June 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n{{multiple image\n| align     = right\n| direction = vertical\n| width     = 200\n| image1    = Westboro Baptist Church protests Michael Sam.jpg\n| caption1  = Members of the [[Westboro Baptist Church]] protest Sam and the [[University of Missouri]].\n| image2    = Stand With Sam WBC counterprotestors.jpg\n| caption2  = Student counter-protesters form a wall in support of Sam.\n}}\nSam is the seventh of eight children born to JoAnn and Michael Alan Sam, Sr. His parents separated when he was young.<ref name=father/> As a child, Sam watched one of his older brothers die from a gunshot wound. Another older brother has been missing since 1998,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.charleyproject.org/cases/s/sam_julian.html |title=Julian Michael Sam |publisher=The Charley Project |date= |accessdate=October 8, 2015}}</ref> and his other two brothers are in prison. A sister who was born before him died in infancy.<ref name=\"OTL\"/> At one point in his childhood, Sam lived in his mother's car.<ref name=father/> He was once accidentally [[mace (spray)|maced]] by police who were arresting one of his brothers.<ref name=haven/>\n\nSam argued with his mother, a [[Jehovah's Witnesses|Jehovah's Witness]], over playing football, as she did not agree with those pursuits. Sam often stayed with friends while in high school; the parents of a classmate gave him a bedroom in their house and had him complete household chores.<ref name=father/> Sam is the first member of his family to attend college.<ref name=nytimes>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/10/sports/michael-sam-college-football-star-says-he-is-gay-ahead-of-nfl-draft.html?hp&_r=0|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|first=John|last=Branch|title=N.F.L. Prospect Michael Sam Proudly Says What Teammates Knew: He's Gay|date=February 9, 2014|accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"OTL\"/>\n\nIn August 2013, Sam took the opportunity of a team introduce-yourself session to inform his Missouri teammates that he was gay, and found them supportive.<ref name=\"OTL\"/> He avoided talking to the media to avoid addressing rumors of his sexuality.<ref name=unheralded/><ref name=accomplishments>{{cite web|url=http://msn.foxsports.com/kansas-city/story/michael-sam-s-career-accomplishments-at-mizzou-won-t-soon-be-forgotten-122413|title=Michael Sam's career accomplishments at Mizzou won't soon be forgotten|first=Nate |last=Latsch|work=FOX Sports|date=December 24, 2013|accessdate=February 13, 2014}}</ref> He [[coming out|came out]] to his father a week before coming out publicly. ''[[The New York Times]]'' wrote that his father, a self-described \"old-school ... man-and-a-woman type of guy\", said \"I don't want my grandkids raised in that kind of environment.\"<ref name=father>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/12/sports/football/for-nfl-prospect-michael-sam-upbringing-was-bigger-challenge-than-coming-out-as-gay.html?hp&_r=0|title=Before Coming Out, a Hard Time Coming Up: Michael Sam's Troubled Upbringing in Texas|first1=Joe|last1=Drape|first2=Steve|last2=Eder|first3=Billy|last3=Witz|newspaper=The New York Times|date=February 11, 2014|accessdate=February 12, 2014}}</ref> His father told the ''[[Galveston Daily News]]'' that he was \"terribly misquoted\", though ''The New York Times'' maintained that he was quoted \"accurately and fairly.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Michael Sam's father denies remarks |date=February 14, 2014 |publisher=ESPN |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/draft2014/story/_/id/10455131/michael-sam-sr-says-was-terribly-misquoted |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6NO9DI5sk?url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/draft2014/story/_/id/10455131/michael-sam-sr-says-was-terribly-misquoted |archivedate=February 14, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn February 9, 2014, in an interview with [[Chris Connelly (journalist)|Chris Connelly]] on [[ESPN]]'s ''[[Outside the Lines]]'', Sam responded to questions about his coming out experience and his status as one of college football's first [[Homosexuality in American football#Players coming out|openly self-acknowledged gay players]].<ref name=\"OTL\"/> At the time, no active NFL player had ever come out publicly.<ref name=nytimes/><ref name=\"OTL\">{{cite news |title=Michael Sam says he's gay |url=http://espn.go.com/espn/otl/story/_/id/10429030/michael-sam-missouri-tigers-says-gay |work=ESPN |first=Chris |last=Connelly |date=February 9, 2014|accessdate=February 9, 2014}}</ref> Anonymous NFL executives told ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'' they expected Sam to fall in the draft as a result of his announcement.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.kansascity.com/2014/02/09/4810967/michael-sam-goes-from-football.html |title=Michael Sam goes from football star to pioneer |date=February 9, 2014 |first=Sam |last=Mellinger |newspaper=The Kansas City Star |accessdate=February 10, 2014}}</ref> Those statements caused [[National Football League Players Association]] executive director [[DeMaurice Smith]] to respond that any team official who anonymously downgrades Sam is \"gutless\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/10437044/demaurice-smith-rips-unnamed-general-managers-downgraded-michael-sam |title=DeMaurice Smith rips unnamed general managers who downgraded Michael Sam |publisher=espn.go.com |date=January 1, 2008 |accessdate=February 14, 2014}}</ref>  From jail, his brother Josh said, \"I'm proud of him for not becoming like me. I still love him, whatever his lifestyle is. He's still my brother and I love him.\"<ref name=haven>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/10453954/michael-sam-safe-havens-football-surrogate-family|title=Michael Sam's safe havens: Football, surrogate family kept him off path of siblings who are dead or jailed|publisher=ESPN|first=Tania |last=Ganguli|date=February 14, 2014|accessdate=February 15, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe week after his ESPN interview, Sam returned to Missouri with the Tigers football team to accept the 2014 Cotton Bowl championship trophy at a ceremony held at the halftime of a [[Missouri Tigers basketball]] game at [[Mizzou Arena]].  Anti-gay activist [[Shirley Phelps-Roper]] and about 15 other members of the [[Westboro Baptist Church]], an organization widely considered a [[hate group]], protested his appearance. Students organized a counter-protest numbering in the thousands,{{#tag:ref|Missouri University police estimated around 500,<ref>{{cite news|title='Stand with Sam' human wall draws large crowd before Tennessee-Missouri basketball game|url=http://www.columbiatribune.com/blogs/behind_the_stripes/stand-with-sam-human-wall-draws-large-crowd-before-tennessee/article_db92cd6c-9686-11e3-8141-001a4bcf6878.html|accessdate=February 20, 2014|newspaper=Columbia Daily Tribune|date=February 15, 2014|first=David |last=Morrison}}</ref> others reported a thousand or more,<ref>{{cite news|last=Latsch |first=Nate |title=Supporters 'Stand With Sam' to block Westboro Baptist Church protest of former Tiger |date=February 15, 2014 |work=FoxSports.com |url=http://msn.foxsports.com/midwest/story/supporters-stand-with-sam-to-block-westboro-baptist-church-protest-of-former-tiger-021514 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Nh6CR5tg?url=http://msn.foxsports.com/midwest/story/supporters-stand-with-sam-to-block-westboro-baptist-church-protest-of-former-tiger-021514 |archivedate=February 27, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Bennett |first=Colette |title=Mizzou stands with Sam, stands down Westboro protesters with human wall |date=February 17, 2014 |work=CNN.com |url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/02/17/us/missouri-sam-westboro-protesters/ |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Nh6MMaao?url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/02/17/us/missouri-sam-westboro-protesters/ |archivedate=February 27, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> while [[ESPN.com]] estimated around 2,000.<ref name=\"Showing How It's Done\"/>|group=lower-alpha}} assembling a \"human wall\" in front of the protesters.<ref name=\"Showing How It's Done\">{{cite news|title=Showing How It's Done Mizzou students protected Michael Sam from seeing church protesters|url=http://espn.go.com/college-football/story/_/id/10466480/mizzou-students-display-true-spirit-supporting-michael-sam|publisher=ESPN|first=Rick|last=Reilly|date=February 18, 2014|accessdate=February 26, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAfter being drafted by the Rams, Sam's emotional reaction to his draft was broadcast live on television, during which he kissed his boyfriend, Vito Cammisano. Reported to have been dating Sam for several months, Cammisano is a fellow alum of the University of Missouri and was a member of the school's swim team.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michael Sam and boyfriend Vito Cammisano party in Las Vegas after NFL draft selection|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/football/michael-sam-boyfriend-revealed-article-1.1788155|work=[[New York Daily News]]|first=Daniel|last=Beekman|date=May 12, 2014|accessdate=May 12, 2014}}</ref> In January 2015, Sam and Cammisano announced their engagement.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Christie|first1=Joel|title=First openly gay NFL player Michael Sam is ENGAGED to his longtime boyfriend 'after a romantic New Years getaway together in Europe'|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2902758/Michael-Sam-longtime-boyfriend-engaged-romantic-New-Years-getaway-Europe.html|accessdate=January 9, 2015|work=[[Mail Online]]|date=January 9, 2015|location=United Kingdom}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Webber|first1=Stephanie|title=Michael Sam Engaged to Boyfriend Vito Cammisano|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/michael-sam-engaged-to-boyfriend-vito-cammisano-201591|accessdate=January 9, 2015|work=[[Us Weekly]]|date=January 9, 2015|location=United States}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Fieldstadt|first=Elisha|title=Michael Sam Confirms His Engagement in a Tweet|date=January 16, 2015|work=NBCNews.com|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/sports/michael-sam-confirms-his-engagement-tweet-n288086|accessdate=January 19, 2015}}</ref> However, the couple ended their relationship in June 2015, although have remained friends.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://instinctmagazine.com/post/michael-sam-vito-cammisano-reunite-support-spirit-day |title=Michael Sam & Vito Cammisano Reunite To Support Spirit Day |work=[[Instinct (magazine)|Instinct]] |date=October 15, 2015 |accessdate=November 4, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2016 Sam spoke with LGBTQ advocacy groups at the [[Missouri State Capitol]] against a bill that would enable discrimination against LGBTQ people and personally lobbied [[Missouri General Assembly|state legislators]].<ref>[https://www.stltoday.com/news/michael-sam-slams-missouri-s-religious-objections-bill/article_455d3b7e-706c-55d3-9d8c-5e4cf783527f.html Michael Sam slams Missouri's religious objections bill]</ref>\n\n===''Dancing with the Stars''===\nOn February 24, 2015, Sam was announced as one of the celebrities to compete on the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 20)|20th season]] of ''Dancing with the Stars''. He partnered with professional dancer [[Peta Murgatroyd]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/dancing-stars-2015-season-20-celebrity-cast-announced/story?id=29166872 |title='Dancing With the Stars' 2015: Season 20 Celebrity Cast Announced \u2013 ABC News |publisher=Abcnews.go.com |date=February 24, 2015 |accessdate=October 8, 2015}}</ref> Sam and Murgatroyd were eliminated in the fourth week of competition and finished in tenth place.<ref>{{cite news|last=Stabile|first=Maria|date=April 6, 2015|url=http://news.lalate.com/2015/04/06/dancing-with-the-stars-2015-results-tonight-michael-sam-gets-dwts-elimination/|title=Dancing with the Stars 2015 results tonight: Michael Sam gets DWTS elimination|work=Lalate News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411041734/http://news.lalate.com/2015/04/06/dancing-with-the-stars-2015-results-tonight-michael-sam-gets-dwts-elimination|archive-date=April 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Honors and accolades==\nSam won the [[Arthur Ashe Courage Award]] at the [[2014 ESPY Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/draft2014/story/_/id/10894871/michael-sam-wins-arthur-ashe-courage-award|title=Michael Sam wins Arthur Ashe Award|publisher=ESPN|date=May 7, 2014|accessdate=October 21, 2014}}</ref> He was named one of ''[[GQ]]''{{'}}s Men of the Year,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.columbiamissourian.com/a/181786/michael-sam-named-one-of-gqs-men-of-the-year/|title=Michael Sam named one of GQ's Men of the Year|work=[[Columbia Missourian]]|date=November 17, 2014|accessdate=November 19, 2014}}</ref> and a finalist for ''Sports Illustrated''{{'}}s [[Sportsman of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.columbiamissourian.com/a/181164/sports-illustrated-makes-michael-sam-a-sportsman-finalist/|title=Sports Illustrated makes Michael Sam a Sportsman finalist|work=Columbia Missourian|first=Erik|last=Hall|date=November 4, 2014|accessdate=November 19, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal bar|Biography|College football|LGBT|Texas}}\n* [[Homosexuality in American football]]\n* [[List of LGBT sportspeople]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/player/michaelsam/2543734/profile|title=Michael Sam, DE|work=NFL.com}}\n*[https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/players/michael-sam-1.html College stats]\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\